+## 3. Active CI & governance guards (in force)
+
+- **On-demand CI:** `workflow_dispatch` on Platform Guardrails and UI Verification.
+- **Backend:** URL-contract test (route + cross-module view-export surface); dependency-direction guard (`contracts/api` & `contracts/domain` must not import `contracts.views`) with a minimal, documented **A3** allowlist (the single existing `api/matching.py` violation).
+- **Frontend:** forbidden/deprecated-import guard — derives its set **from the canonical `CAREON_COMPONENT_INVENTORY.md`** (no second list), reports an explicit "nothing to enforce" when empty, hard-fails on missing inventory; diff-scoped design-token governance — reuses the canonical token RULES, checks only added lines, fails in CI when the diff base is missing.
+- **Process:** Definition of Ready + Definition of Done in `.github/pull_request_template.md`; component register designated source of truth.
+
+## 4. Canonical document hierarchy
+
+- `CAREON_DESIGN_SYSTEM_V1.md` — design principles, tokens, mandatory implementation rules.
+- `CAREON_COMPONENT_INVENTORY.md` — canonical component register (Governance status × Planned action).
+- `CAREON_SCREEN_ARCHETYPE_MAP.md` — page archetypes and reference pages.
+- `CAREON_DESIGN_DEBT_REGISTER.md` — known deviations and migration work.
+- `CAREON_UI_CONTRACT.md` — historical/retired. `CAREON_PAGE_PATTERNS.md` — subordinate to the design system + archetype map. Duplication report — supporting analysis.
+
+## 5. `CareCommandPrimitives` status
+
+**Needs consolidation** (Planned action: Review / Merge). Actively used by **21 production consumers**; functional overlap with `CareDesignPrimitives`. **Not** deprecated, **not** forbidden, **not** removed, no consumers migrated.
+
+**The canonical direction is decided** (the read-only comparison is done): `CareDesignPrimitives` is the approved canonical target architecture; `CareCommandPrimitives` is `Needs consolidation`; migration of the 21 consumers is **planned but not started**; `CareCommandPrimitives` becomes `Deprecated` **only after** replacement capabilities exist in `CareDesignPrimitives` **and** all consumers are migrated. The choice is made — only the migration is deferred. Conditions in force (documented in the inventory): no new primitives added to it; no new consumers without explicit motivation.
+
+## 6. `CareDesignPrimitives` status
+
+Canonical target design system (token-strict, tested, a11y-instrumented, single barrel import path). M0 added the interactive metric capability it lacked (`CareInteractiveMetricCard`, `CareInteractiveMetricStrip`) as additive exports (not yet consumed). Passive metrics remain separate (`CareKPICard`, `CareMetricBadge`).
+
+**API note (documented, no code change):** `CareInteractiveMetricCard` is controlled — `pressed` is owned by the parent and `onPressedChange` is **optional** in the type, but **interactive consumers must provide `onPressedChange`** (a clickable card without it goes nowhere). This guidance is recorded in the component JSDoc, the inventory row, and the D2 section of `CAREON_DESIGN_SYSTEM_V1.md`. The API is intentionally left unchanged.
+
