+
+## 8. Deliberately NOT done this phase
+
+M1–M4 consumer migrations; `contracts/views.py` decomposition; matching consolidation; `models.py` decomposition; pagination; any `CareWorkRow` change; `CareCommandPrimitives` removal/deprecation; consumer migrations; page redesigns; backend/router/API changes; new features.
+
+## 9. Remaining risks & technical debt (carried into future phases)
+
+- **`contracts/views.py`** god-module (~8.2k LOC) + inverted `api/matching.py → contracts.views` dependency (currently allowlisted under A3).
+- **A/B duplication** — `CareCommandPrimitives` (21 consumers) overlaps the canonical `CareDesignPrimitives`. The canonical direction is **decided** (`CareDesignPrimitives`); only the consumer migration is deferred (planned, not started).
+- **`CareCommandPrimitives` has no tests/stories** and carries hardcoded styling (`bg-white`, rgba shadow, `yellow-*`, raw sizes).
+- **`LoginPage.tsx`** off-token (37 inline styles, 27 hex).
+- **`models.py`** (~4.6k LOC) — deferred.
+- **Environment:** committed `db.sqlite3` lags migrations; the working-tree mount denies `rm`/unlink (stale `.git` locks, un-removable stray doc copies) — git hygiene must be done on a real machine.
+
+## 10. Recommended next product/engineering step
+
+The next active step is **determined by product priority**, and any next step must now be executed **within the new governance**: the Definition of Ready/Done, the canonical document hierarchy, the page archetypes, and the component standards established in this phase (incl. the active CI guards).
+
+Available, fully-planned options (none is automatically next; choose by priority):
+
+- **`contracts/views.py` decomposition** — a planned backend option (Phase 0/1: containerized test env + guardrail tests; also resolves the inverted A3 dependency). High leverage, but optional and priority-driven.
+- **Frontend M1** — the two shell-only page migrations (`PlacementPage`, `AccessDeniedPage`); low risk; read-only plan retained.
+- **Matching consolidation** / **`models.py` decomposition** — later, per the roadmap.
+
+The M1 plan (`CAREON_M1_PLAN.md`) is retained **only as a future, read-only plan** and is not an exit criterion of this phase.
